#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading online"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:12
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading &slema;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:19
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&suse; offers an intuitive graphical and a simple command-line tool to "
"upgrade a running system to a new service pack. Both provide support for "
"<quote>rollback</quote> of service packs and more. This chapter provides "
"step-by-step instructions on how to perform a service pack upgrade using "
"these tools."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&suse; offers a command-line tool to upgrade a running system to a new "
"version. The tool provides support for <quote>rollback</quote> to an older "
"release. This chapter provides step-by-step instructions on how to perform a "
"system upgrade."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:36
#, no-c-format
msgid "Conceptual overview"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:38
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&suse; releases new service packs for the &sle; family at regular intervals. "
"To make it easy for customers to migrate to a new service pack and minimize "
"downtime, &suse; supports migrating online while the system is running."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:44
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&suse; releases new version of &slema; at regular intervals. To make it easy "
"for customers to migrate to a new minor version and minimize downtime, "
"&suse; supports migrating online while the system is running."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:50
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Starting with &slea;&nbsp;12, &yast; Wagon has been replaced by &yast; "
"migration (GUI) and Zypper migration (command line). This has the following "
"advantages:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:56
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&slema; uses <emphasis>transactional updates</emphasis> to upgrade from one "
"version to the next. This has the following advantages:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:67
#, no-c-format
msgid "The system is always in a defined state until the first RPM is updated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "Canceling is possible until the first RPM is updated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "Simple recovery if there is an error."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:82
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to do a <quote>rollback</quote> via system tools&mdash;no "
"backup or restore needed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:88
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use of all active repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "The ability to skip a service pack"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:100
#, no-c-format
msgid "Online migration not supported for major releases"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The online migration is <emphasis>only</emphasis> supported for migrating "
"between service packs. Online migration is <emphasis>not supported</"
"emphasis> for upgrading to new major releases. For details, see <xref "
"linkend=\"cha-upgrade-paths\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the offline migration to upgrade to a new major release. For details, "
"see <xref linkend=\"cha-upgrade-offline\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:114
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading &smlm; clients"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:115
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the system to upgrade is a &smlm; client, it cannot be upgraded by &yast; "
"online migration or <command>zypper migration</command> . Use the "
"<citetitle>Client Migration</citetitle> procedure instead. It is described "
"in the <link xlink:href=\"https://documentation.suse.com/multi-linux-manager/"
"\"> <citetitle>&smlm; Upgrade Guide</citetitle></link> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:125
#, no-c-format
msgid "Service pack migration workflow"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A service pack migration can be executed by either &yast;, <command>zypper</"
"command> , or &ay;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before you can start a service pack migration, your system must be "
"registered at the &scc; or a local &rmt; server. &smlm; can also be used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Regardless of the method, a service pack migration consists of the following "
"steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:145
#, no-c-format
msgid "Find possible migration targets on your registered systems."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:150
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select one migration target."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:155
#, no-c-format
msgid "Request and enable new repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "Run the migration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:166
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The list of migration targets depends on the products you have installed and "
"registered. If you have an extension installed for which the new SP is not "
"yet available, it could be that no migration target is offered to you."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The list of migration targets available for your host will always be "
"retrieved from the &scc; and depend on products or extensions installed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:178
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading to a new release"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:181
#, no-c-format
msgid "&scc; and Internet connection"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:182
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the system you want to upgrade is registered with the &scc;, make sure to "
"have an Internet connection during the following procedure."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:188
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If your system is registered, proceed as described in <xref linkend=\"proc-"
"uprade-registered\"/> . If your system system is not registered, change the "
"repositories to point to the &productnumber; and run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:193
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;transactional-update dup"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:196
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrade to a newer version"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:198
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The upgrade procedure is performed by calling the <command>transactional-"
"update</command> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:202
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"   transactional-update migration\n"
"   "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:207
#, no-c-format
msgid "A new snapshot is created."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:212
#, no-c-format
msgid "Current repositories are refreshed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:217
#, no-c-format
msgid "A list of available migration targets is displayed. Enter a number."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:222
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A list of packages to be installed or updated is displayed. Press "
"<literal>y</literal> to continue with the upgrade procedure."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:228
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To complete the upgrade, reboot your system and boot into the target version."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:236
#, no-c-format
msgid "Canceling service pack migration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:238
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A service pack migration can only be canceled at specific stages during the "
"migration process:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:245
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Until the package upgrade starts, there are only minimal changes on the "
"system, such as changes to services and repositories. Restore <filename>/etc/"
"zypp/repos.d/*</filename> to revert to the previous state."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the package upgrade starts, you can revert to the previous state by "
"using a Snapper snapshot (see <xref linkend=\"cha-snapper\"/> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:258
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the migration target was selected, &scc; changes the repository data. "
"To revert this state manually, use <command>SUSEConnect</command> <option>--"
"rollback</option> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:267
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reverting the migration process"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:269
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a new release does not work for you, &slema; supports reverting the "
"system to the state before the migration process was started by using the "
"<command>transactional-update rollback</command> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:275
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The detailed procedure for a system rollback is described in <xref "
"linkend=\"sec-rollback-procedure\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:281
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading with the online migration tool (&yast;)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:283
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To perform a service pack migration with &yast;, use the <guimenu>Online "
"Migration</guimenu> tool. By default, &yast; does not install any packages "
"from a third-party repository. If a package was installed from a third-party "
"repository, &yast; prevents packages from being replaced with the same "
"package coming from &suse;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:299
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Deactivate all unused extensions on your registration server to avoid future "
"dependency conflicts. If you forget an extension, &yast; will later detect "
"unused extension repositories and deactivate them."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:329
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Run &yast; online update to get the latest package updates for your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:335
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Install the package <package>yast2-migration</package> and its dependencies "
"(in &yast; under <menuchoice> <guimenu>Software</guimenu> <guimenu>Software "
"Management</guimenu> </menuchoice> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:342
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Restart &yast;, otherwise the newly installed module will not be shown in "
"the control center."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:348
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &yast;, choose <guimenu>Online Migration</guimenu> (depending on the "
"version of &productname; that you are upgrading from, this module is "
"categorized under either <guimenu>System</guimenu> or <guimenu>Software</"
"guimenu> ). &yast; will show possible migration targets and a summary. If "
"more than one migration target is available for your system, select one from "
"the list."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:358
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select one migration target from the list and proceed with <guimenu>Next</"
"guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:364
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the migration tool offers update repositories, it is recommended to "
"proceed with <guimenu>Yes</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:370
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<remark>toms 2015-09-09: FATE#319140</remark> If the online migration tool "
"finds obsolete repositories from DVD or a local server, it is highly "
"recommended to disable them. Obsolete repositories are for a previous "
"service pack. Old repositories from &scc; or &rmt; are removed automatically."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:377
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the registration server does not offer migrations for a module or "
"extension, its repository configuration will remain unchanged. This usually "
"happens with 3rd party repositories such as the <guimenu>&nvidia; Compute "
"Module</guimenu> that are not specific to a product version or service pack. "
"If necessary, you can manually check the repository configuration after the "
"migration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:387
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check the summary and proceed with the migration by clicking <guimenu>Next</"
"guimenu> . Confirm with <guimenu>Start Update</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:394
#, no-c-format
msgid "After the successful migration restart your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:401
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading with Zypper"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:403
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To perform a service pack migration with Zypper, use the command-line tool "
"<command>zypper</command> <option>migration</option> from the package "
"<package>zypper-migration-plugin</package> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:411
#, no-c-format
msgid "To start the service pack migration, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:417
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are logged in to a GNOME session running on the machine you are going "
"to update, switch to a text console. Running the update from within a GNOME "
"session is not recommended. Note that this does not apply when being logged "
"in from a remote machine (unless you are running a VNC session with GNOME)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:426
#, no-c-format
msgid "Register your &sle; machine if you have not done so:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:429
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;<command>SUSEConnect</command> --regcode "
"<replaceable>YOUR_REGISTRATION_CODE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:446
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start the migration:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:449
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>zypper migration</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:450
#, no-c-format
msgid "Some notes about the migration process:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:455
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If more than one migration target is available for your system, Zypper "
"allows you to select one SP from the list. This is the same as skipping one "
"or more SPs. Keep in mind, online migration for base products (&slsa;, "
"&sleda;) remains available only between the SPs of a major version."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, Zypper uses the option <option>--no-allow-vendor-change</option> "
"which is passed to <command>zypper</command> <option>dup</option> . If a "
"package was installed from a third-party repository, this option prevents "
"packages from being replaced with the same package coming from &suse;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:473
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<remark>toms 2015-09-09: FATE#319140</remark> If Zypper finds obsolete "
"repositories coming from DVD or a local server, it is highly recommended to "
"disable them. Old &scc; or &rmt; repositories are removed automatically."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:483
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Review all the changes, especially the packages that are going to be "
"removed. Proceed by typing <literal>y</literal> (the exact number of "
"packages to upgrade can vary on your system):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:488
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"266 packages to upgrade, 54 to downgrade, 17 new, 8 to reinstall, 5 to "
"remove, 1 to change arch.\n"
"Overall download size: 285.1 MiB. Already cached: 0 B  After the operation, "
"additional 139.8 MiB will be used.\n"
"Continue? [y/n/? shows all options] (y):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:491
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the <keycombo> <keycap function=\"shift\"/> <keycap function=\"pageup\"/"
"> </keycombo> or <keycombo> <keycap function=\"shift\"/> <keycap "
"function=\"pagedown\"/> </keycombo> keys to scroll in your shell."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:498
#, no-c-format
msgid "After successful migration restart your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:505
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading with plain Zypper"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:507
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If your system is not registered because you do not have access to the "
"Internet or a registration server, migrating to a new service pack is not "
"possible with &yast; Migration or <command>zypper migration</command> . In "
"this case you can still migrate to a new service pack with plain Zypper and "
"some manual interactions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:516
#, no-c-format
msgid "For unregistered systems only"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:517
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This migration path to a new service pack is <emphasis>only</emphasis> "
"supported for unregistered systems that do not have access to the Internet "
"or a registration server. This may, for example, be the case for machines in "
"a specially protected network. If you have a registered system, use &yast; "
"or Zypper migration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:527
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installation sources"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:528
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This migration path requires that the system you are going to migrate has "
"access to the installation sources. For example, this can be done by setting "
"up an &rmt; server or an SLP server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:533
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is also required that the system has access to an up-to-date update "
"repository for the installed product version."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:541
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are logged in to a graphical session running on the machine you are "
"going to migrate, log out of that session and switch to a text console. "
"Running the update from within a graphical session is not recommended. Note "
"that this does not apply when being logged in from a remote machine (unless "
"you are running a VNC session with X)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:550
#, no-c-format
msgid "Update the package management tools:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:553
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>zypper</command> patch --updatestack-only"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:556
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that all &productname; repository configuration files in "
"<filename>/etc/zypp/repos.d/</filename> use the variable "
"<varname>$releasever</varname> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:560
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.user;<command>grep baseurl /etc/zypp/repos.d/*.repo</command>\n"
"/etc/zypp/repos.d/rmt.repo:baseurl=https://rmt.&exampledomain;/repo/SUSE/"
"Products/SLE-<replaceable>15-SP5</replaceable>-Product-SLES/x86_64/product/\n"
"/etc/zypp/repos.d/updates.repo:baseurl=https://updates.suse.com/SUSE/"
"Products/SLE-Product-SLES/<replaceable>$releasever</replaceable>/x86_64/"
"product[...]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:563
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this example, the file <filename>updates.repo</filename> uses the "
"variable, while <filename>rmt.repo</filename> hardcodes the version string "
"<literal>15-SP5</literal> . To replace all occurrences of <literal>15-SP5</"
"literal> with <varname>$releasever</varname> across all repository "
"configuration files, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:569
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;<command>sed -i 's/15-SP5/${releasever}/g' /etc/zypp/repos.d/*."
"repo</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:570
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If necessary, repeat this command with different version strings to ensure "
"all repository configuration files get updated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:576
#, no-c-format
msgid "Check if all repositories are configured correctly:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:579
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;<command>zypper --releasever=&product-dsc-url-substring; repos -"
"u</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:580
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You should now see <literal>&product-dsc-url-substring;</literal> in the "
"repository URLs. Note that some third-party repositories may be unversioned. "
"It is assumed that they work for all &productname; releases."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:587
#, no-c-format
msgid "Switch and refresh all repositories to &productnumber;:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:590
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;<command>zypper --releasever=&product-dsc-url-substring; "
"refresh -f -s</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:591
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case updating a repository fails, double-check whether you entered the "
"wrong URL. If the problem cannot be fixed, it is recommended to disable the "
"failing repository."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:598
#, no-c-format
msgid "Test the migration:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:601
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;<command>zypper --releasever=&product-dsc-url-substring; dup -D "
"--no-allow-vendor-change --no-recommends</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:602
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The parameter <option>-D</option> will perform a dry run that simulates the "
"migration without actually changing the system. If problems occur, fix them "
"before proceeding."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:607
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The option <option>-no-allow-vendor-change</option> prevents third-party "
"packages from replacing RPM packages from the base system. The option "
"<option>--no-recommends</option> ensures that packages deselected during "
"initial installation will not be added again."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:614
#, no-c-format
msgid "Execute the full distribution upgrade:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:617
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;<command>zypper --releasever=&product-dsc-url-substring; dup --"
"no-allow-vendor-change --no-recommends</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:618
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With the above command, zypper downloads all packages in advance&mdash;which "
"is more reliable if your Internet connection may fail. To download and "
"install packages in heaps, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:622
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;<command>zypper zypper --releasever=&product-dsc-url-substring; "
"dup --no-allow-vendor-change --no-recommends --download-in-heaps</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:623
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the distribution update is finished, &productname; sets the "
"<varname>$releasever</varname> variable to the new version and you no longer "
"need to specify it with the <option>--releasever</option> option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:630
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reboot your system after successful migration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:637
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rolling back a service pack"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:639
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a service pack does not work for you, &sle; supports reverting the system "
"to the state before the service pack migration was started. Prerequisite is "
"a Btrfs root partition with snapshots enabled (this has been the default "
"since &slsa;&nbsp;12). See <xref linkend=\"cha-snapper\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:648
#, no-c-format
msgid "Get a list of all Snapper snapshots:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:651
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;snapper list"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:652
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Review the output to locate the snapshot that was created immediately before "
"the service pack migration was started. The column <guimenu>Description</"
"guimenu> contains a corresponding statement and the snapshot is marked as "
"<literal>important</literal> in the column <guimenu>Userdata</guimenu> . "
"Memorize the snapshot number from the column <guimenu>#</guimenu> and its "
"date from the column <guimenu>Date</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:662
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Reboot the system. From the boot menu, select <guimenu>Start boot loader "
"from a read-only snapshot</guimenu> and then choose the snapshot with the "
"date and number you memorized in the previous step. A second boot menu (the "
"one from the snapshot) is loaded. Select the entry starting with &slsa;&nbsp;"
"&productnumber; and boot it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:671
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The system boots into the previous state with the system partition mounted "
"read-only. Log in as &rootuser; and check whether you have chosen the "
"correct snapshot. Also make sure everything works as expected. Note that "
"since the root file system is mounted read-only, restrictions in "
"functionality may apply."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:678
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case of problems or if you have booted the wrong snapshot, reboot and "
"choose a different snapshot to boot from&mdash;up to this point no permanent "
"changes have been made. If the snapshot is correct and works as expected, "
"make the change permanent by running the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:684
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;snapper rollback"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:685
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Reboot the machine. On the boot screen, choose the default boot entry to "
"reboot into the reinstated system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:691
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check if the repository configuration has been properly reset. Furthermore, "
"check if all products are properly registered. If either one is not the "
"case, updating the system at a later point in time may no longer work, or "
"the system may be updated using the wrong package repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:698
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure the system can access the Internet before starting this procedure."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:704
#, no-c-format
msgid "Refresh services and repositories by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:707
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper ref -fs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:710
#, no-c-format
msgid "Get a list of active repositories by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:713
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper lr"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:714
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Carefully check the output of this command. No services and repositories "
"that were added for the update should be listed. For example, if you are "
"rolling back from &slsa;&nbsp;&productnumber; to &slsa;&product-ga; GA, the "
"list must contain the <literal>SLES&product-ga;-GA</literal> repositories, "
"and not the <literal>SLES&product-ga;-SP&product-sp;</literal> repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:722
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If wrong repositories are listed, delete them and, if necessary, replace "
"them with the versions matching your product or service pack version. For a "
"list of repositories for the supported migration paths refer to <xref "
"linkend=\"sec-upgrade-background-modules\"/> . (Note that manual "
"intervention should not be necessary, as the repositories should be updated "
"automatically, but it is a best practice to verify and make any necessary "
"corrections.)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:733
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Last, check the registration status for all products installed by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:737
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;SUSEConnect --status"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:738
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All products should be reported as being <literal>Registered</literal> . If "
"this is not the case, repair the registration by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:742
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;SUSEConnect --rollback"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:748
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you have successfully reverted the system to the state that was captured "
"immediately before the service pack migration was started."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:754
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading with &smlm;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:756
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&smlm; is a server solution for providing updates, patches, and security "
"fixes for &sle; clients. It comes with a set of tools and a Web-based user "
"interface for management tasks. See <link xlink:href=\"https://www.suse.com/"
"products/multi-linux-manager/\"/> for more information about &smlm;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:765
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SP Migration allows migrating from one Service Pack (SP) to another within "
"one major version (for example, from &slsa;&nbsp;&product-ga;&nbsp;GA to "
"&slsa;&nbsp;&product-ga;&nbsp;SP&product-sp;)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:775
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading from &opensuse; Leap to &productname;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:776
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can upgrade an &opensuse; Leap installation to &productname;. To find "
"out which Leap versions are supported for migration, refer to <xref "
"linkend=\"sec-upgrade-paths-supported\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:787
#, no-c-format
msgid "Not all &opensuse; packages can be migrated"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:788
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&opensuse; provides more packages than &productname;. Most of the additional "
"packages are available through &ph; and will be migrated. Any additional "
"packages that are not available through &ph; will no longer receive updates "
"after the migration and should therefore be removed afterward."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:794
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that all packages you need for operating your system are available "
"in the &productname; and &ph; repositories. For more information about &ph;, "
"refer to <link xlink:href=\"https://packagehub.suse.com/\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:802
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgraging with <command>yast2 migration</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:803
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following procedure is similar to <xref linkend=\"sec-upgrade-online-"
"yast\"/> , but requires some additional steps. Before executing this "
"procedure on a production system, we recommend to first run it on a test "
"system that replicates your production setup."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:810
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Upgrading &opensuse; Leap to &productname; with with <command>yast2 "
"migration</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:816
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Close all unused applications and switch to a TTY, for example by pressing "
"<keycombo><keycap function=\"control\"/> <keycap function=\"alt\"/"
"><keycap>F1</keycap></keycombo> . Then log in as &rootuser;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:824
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Install the <package>yast2-migration</package> and <package>rollback-helper</"
"package> packages:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:828
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>zypper in yast2-migration rollback-helper</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:835
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>systemctl enable rollback</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:838
#, no-c-format
msgid "Register the system with the &scc;:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:841
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>yast2 registration</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:844
#, no-c-format
msgid "Perform the migration:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:847
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>yast2 migration</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:848
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case of package conflicts, &yast; presents a list of resolutions to "
"choose from."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:857
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>reboot</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:873
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading with <command>yast2 migration_sle</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:874
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A simplified migration from &opensuse; Leap to &productname; is available as "
"a technology preview as of Leap 15.4."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:879
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Upgrading &opensuse; Leap to &productname; with <command>yast2 "
"migration_sle</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:880
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To migrate from &opensuse; Leap to &productname;, perform the following "
"steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:885
#, no-c-format
msgid "Close all unused applications (recommended)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:890
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Install the <package>yast2-migration-sle</package> and <package>rollback-"
"helper</package> packages:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:894
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;<command>zypper in yast2-migration-sle rollback-helper</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:897
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enable the <systemitem class=\"service\">rollback-helper</systemitem> "
"service:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:901
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>systemctl enable rollback</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:904
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open &yast; and select <menuchoice><guimenu>Software</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Online Migration</guimenu></menuchoice> or run:"
