#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:909
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The wizard will guide you through the migration process. If there are "
"pending updates, they can be installed before registering the system. To "
"register, enter your registration code and e-mail address. To register with "
"a local &rmt; server, provide its URL instead of the registration code and "
"leave the e-mail address empty."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:916
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the system is registered, the &productname; repositories will be added "
"and the &slea; packages will be installed to replace the &opensuse; ones."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:923
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reboot the system:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:926
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>reboot</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:929
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You have now successfully migrated your system to &productname;. Continue "
"with <xref linkend=\"cha-upgrade-finish\"/> and remove orphaned packages to "
"ensure you are running a fully supported &sle; installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:934
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you run into a problem after the migration, you can revert the migration "
"like a service pack upgrade. For instructions, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"upgrade-online-rollback\"/> ."
